Renowned musician Yvonne Chaka Chaka has described being honoured at the upcoming 2017 BET Awards as a great honour to be respected for her talent. BET announced early this week announced that SA s Yvonne Chaka Chaka would be honoured with the 2017 BET International Global Good Star and Power award.Speaking on her recognition she said she was initially shocked when she heard the news but is deeply humbled to be recognised by a brand that she loves. I love BET I watch their channels but I always thought it was more for the young people. So when I was told that I am nominated I was deeply humbled because they are recognising me for respecting my talent and the responsibility it comes with it she said.Yvonne added that she remembers watching US musician Chaka Khan being honoured in 2013 and that she never imagined she would one day be on that list. Knowing the power of my talent helped me to be able to help people. Most of my work to advocate for education and good health has been done in the continent but it was only because people already knew who Yvonne Chaka Chaka was that I got the opportunity she said.The musician said she hoped young artists learn that pursuing your dreams and knowing that your talent can help change other people s lives is rewarding.Yvonne who has been in studio for the past 18 months recording her album says she will be leaving for Los Angeles on June 20 a week before the ceremony on June 29.This year, Yvonne Chaka Chaka shares the same award with Ilwad Elman Somali, a Somali-Canadian social activist.